    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-04-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="532" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Señor Garcia</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Clarendon Hotel,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">New York,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-04-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 29, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have had the honor to receive your
                                excellency’s note of yesterday, inclosing the reply of your
                                department to a note of Mr. Ignacio Gomez, the Nicaragua
                                plenipotentiary, communicating to your excellency the offer of his
                                government to intercede between the allied republics and Spain to
                                effect a permanent peace.</p>
                <p>The sincere and friendly interest which your excellency has ever
                                shown for the conclusion of that war, and which you repeat in your
                                reply, will be highly appreciated by my government.</p>
                <p>On renewing to your excellency the assurances of my personal
                                consideration, I subscribe myself your attentive servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOSÉ ANTONIO G. Y GAECIA.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">, &amp;c<hi rend="italic">.,
                                            &amp;</hi>c<hi rend="italic">.,</hi> &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
